                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1192-2">AMS, III, 254-83 ; BHO, 194 (armenien 193).
DHGE, XIII, col. 1168 s.v. Cyrice (R. van Doren).
Vies des saints, V, 16 juin, 260-61.
BSO, I, 491 (J. Rabbi).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1192">Cyriacus and his mother <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1332">Juliette</persName> were martyrs. They were martyred
          under Diocletian in either Iconium, Tarsus, or Antioch, together with many others.
          Juliette was martyred with her son of three years of age, Cyriacus.</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">with Juliette</note>
